node.text:
A few months back at BB HQ, we got a voicemail from Lynsey’s friend Francesca. She shared Lynsey and Nora’s journey and we knew we wanted to help. Going forward, Baby Bling will commemorate Nora’s birthday with a donation to the CICU at Primary Children’s Hospital every year.

“Baby Bling Bows were the only bows that were comfortable on Nora, and the only thing I bought for her before she was born. I loved being able to “dress” her in a bow and matching swaddle each day; these bows helped create a sense of normalcy for my baby in a very abnormal situation… Thank you Baby Bling!”

node.text:
Meet Courtney & Sabrina, our bow peeps for pride month! We are so excited to share their family with the BB community. Join us in lifting, supporting, and loving all of our LGBTQ+ bow peeps this month, and always!

“My reason for every season, but especially during Pride.

Representation, normalization, and visibility of families that look like ours is extremely important all year, but even more during Pride.

Although I was exposed to same sex couples growing up, that is not the same for many in our community, Sabrina included. So to our non-LGBTQ+ families, please share families that look like ours with your children. Show the beauty in all family make-ups.

Our goal is to make our love and family more visible in every light; to show that even through our different family dynamics, we truly aren’t that different after all.

Happy Pride Month!”

-  @mamas_triplet_love 

#pridemonth

node.text:
🤍

We are SO excited to introduce Rose Fabian and her beautiful daughter Ava, and to learn more about the Microtia and Deaf/Hard of Hearing community. We hope you will take the time to watch this video, and connect with Ava and Rose, our Bow Peeps! 

 “Ever since I started to come back around from my postpartum depression, I knew that I had to share our story and do all I could to raise awareness and advocate for Ava and the Microtia and Deaf/Hard of Hearing Communities. People do not know or understand most things until they learn from personal experience or are exposed to people or situations. We love Baby Bling - they were our first bows - and all that you do to continually show inclusion. One thing that all of us Microtia mamas struggle with is seeing babies that look like ours in ads for brands, tv and other social media channels. I am sure this is the case with moms and families with children that have other conditions as well. This is HUGE on so many levels. I cannot even explain my family's gratitude.”

Rose Fabian @xoxoavajuliette

Aesha Lee
